241
00:19:40.313 --> 00:19:42.858
the most secure computer
systems ever designed.

242
00:19:42.882 --> 00:19:44.660
( scoffs )
He's a hacker.

243
00:19:44.684 --> 00:19:46.195
If I'm right.
he's<i> the</i> hacker.

244
00:19:46.219 --> 00:19:49.632
<i>CIA's been chasing</i>
<i>their tails for years</i>
<i>trying to find this guy.</i>

245
00:19:49.656 --> 00:19:52.801
The online fanboys.
they call him Job.

246
00:19:52.825 --> 00:19:56.305
But nobody knows for sure
who he really is.

247
00:19:56.329 --> 00:19:59.630
<i>( touch tones beeping )</i>

248
00:20:01.701 --> 00:20:04.368
Lucas:
<i>You find him?</i>

249
00:20:04.804 --> 00:20:08.250
Over the last 12 hours.
there's been a flurry
of cellular activity.

250
00:20:08.274 --> 00:20:11.320
<i>all originating</i>
<i>from phones registered</i>
<i>to the 215 area code.</i>

251
00:20:11.344 --> 00:20:14.924
- Philadelphia.
- Transmissions are localized
to the towers to the south.

252
00:20:14.948 --> 00:20:18.861
There's a lot of buildings
there. but only one
abandoned high school.

253
00:20:18.885 --> 00:20:22.987
- <i>Address?</i>
<i>- 57 Broad Creek Road.</i>

254
00:20:23.790 --> 00:20:25.790
Okay.

255
00:20:26.693 --> 00:20:27.903
Listen. Job...

256
00:20:27.927 --> 00:20:30.962
This was the last time.

257
00:20:48.381 --> 00:20:50.492
( groans )

258
00:20:50.516 --> 00:20:53.262
Well. look who's
finally winded.

259
00:20:53.286 --> 00:20:54.863
Jesus Christ.
you're hit.

260
00:20:54.887 --> 00:20:56.365
Get the fuck off
my Baughman chair.

261
00:20:56.389 --> 00:20:58.767
Do you know how hard
it is to get blood out
of chenille upholstery?

262
00:20:58.791 --> 00:21:01.937
Hey. do me a favor.
Shut the fuck up.
would you?

263
00:21:01.961 --> 00:21:04.428
Stay here.

264
00:21:05.765 --> 00:21:08.244
<i>This place is completely</i>
<i>off the grid.</i>

265
00:21:08.268 --> 00:21:09.645
If Dalton knew about it.
don't you think

266
00:21:09.669 --> 00:21:14.005
he would have
told you when he gave you
your marching orders?

267
00:21:30.356 --> 00:21:32.568
How long you been
under Dalton's thumb?

268
00:21:32.592 --> 00:21:34.703
Too long.
How do you know him?

269
00:21:34.727 --> 00:21:38.274
I have a unique skill set.
In a rare lapse in judgment.

270
00:21:38.298 --> 00:21:40.609
I rendered services
to your former boss.

271
00:21:40.633 --> 00:21:43.734
<i>thinking he was</i>
<i>the real deal.</i>

272
00:21:44.470 --> 00:21:46.048
He wasn't?

273
00:21:46.072 --> 00:21:48.651
Well. they never are.

274
00:21:48.675 --> 00:21:49.952
I stick to criminals now.

275
00:21:49.976 --> 00:21:53.422
At least you know
where you stand
with a criminal.

276
00:21:53.446 --> 00:21:56.781
So what's your story?

277
00:21:57.383 --> 00:21:59.361
Mmm. let me guess.

278
00:21:59.385 --> 00:22:02.464
Dalton got
to you when you
were at rock bottom.

279
00:22:02.488 --> 00:22:04.533
Told you he could
make you something more.

280
00:22:04.557 --> 00:22:07.903
Man does have
a way of getting
inside your head.

281
00:22:07.927 --> 00:22:08.971
Happens
to the best of us.

282
00:22:08.995 --> 00:22:11.940
You said
you could help me
get away from him.

283
00:22:11.964 --> 00:22:13.442
How?

284
00:22:13.466 --> 00:22:16.445
He can't kill us
if he can't find us.

285
00:22:16.469 --> 00:22:19.014
- He can find me.
- He can try.

286
00:22:19.038 --> 00:22:21.717
He got access
to satellites. databases.

287
00:22:21.741 --> 00:22:25.521
and custom software
that can locate almost
anybody anywhere.

288
00:22:25.545 --> 00:22:29.914
But who the fuck
do you think designed
that software?

289
00:22:33.419 --> 00:22:34.630
<i>( keyboard clicking )</i>

290
00:22:34.654 --> 00:22:36.498
By the time I'm done
doing my thing.

291
00:22:36.522 --> 00:22:39.868
you are going to be
a fucking ghost.

292
00:22:39.892 --> 00:22:43.706
Now. let's start
with your name.

293
00:22:43.730 --> 00:22:46.397
( grunts )

294
00:22:50.636 --> 00:22:52.536
( grunts )

295
00:22:55.575 --> 00:22:58.509
( groans )

296
00:23:20.833 --> 00:23:23.645
Sheriff's Department!
Drop your weapons.
Drop 'em!

297
00:23:23.669 --> 00:23:25.647
- Put 'em down!
- Drop your gun.

298
00:23:25.671 --> 00:23:26.648
- Fuck you.
- Brock!

299
00:23:26.672 --> 00:23:28.016
- Emily. you all right?
- She's fine.

300
00:23:28.040 --> 00:23:29.985
