shot full of holes.

303
00:23:33.446 --> 00:23:34.990
- Yeah. right back at you.
- Nobody's getting shot.

304
00:23:35.014 --> 00:23:37.860
- Hood.
- Now. there's a voice
of reason.

305
00:23:37.884 --> 00:23:42.853
- <i>And you are?</i>
<i>- Sheriff Lucas Hood.</i>

306
00:23:45.158 --> 00:23:47.725
Sheriff.

307
00:23:54.534 --> 00:23:57.513
Well. then.
Sheriff Hood.

308
00:23:57.537 --> 00:24:00.438
do you have
a solution in mind?

309
00:24:03.476 --> 00:24:06.610
We're only here
for the woman.

310
00:24:08.080 --> 00:24:10.815
And Mr. Proctor?

311
00:24:11.717 --> 00:24:14.997
Whatever's going on
between you and him.

312
00:24:15.021 --> 00:24:16.765
that's your business.

313
00:24:16.789 --> 00:24:20.758
Oh. now. that sounds
too good to be true.

314
00:24:22.995 --> 00:24:25.763
Do we have a deal?

315
00:24:27.467 --> 00:24:28.644
Let the girl go.

316
00:24:28.668 --> 00:24:30.746
Emily:
<i>Wait. what the hell</i>
<i>are you talking about?</i>

317
00:24:30.770 --> 00:24:32.714
- You can't do that.
- Emily. let's go.

318
00:24:32.738 --> 00:24:34.116
- No. I'm not leaving.
- Emily!

319
00:24:34.140 --> 00:24:37.119
- They're gonna kill him.
- Get the fuck out!

320
00:24:37.143 --> 00:24:40.689
Let's go.
Emily. come on.

321
00:24:40.713 --> 00:24:42.491
Come on.
Let's go. come on.

322
00:24:42.515 --> 00:24:45.850
It's all right.
Come on. let's go.

323
00:24:56.863 --> 00:24:59.830
<i>( door closes )</i>

324
00:25:02.034 --> 00:25:04.668
Oh. shit.

325
00:25:05.771 --> 00:25:08.951
- <i>What. did you follow us?</i>
<i>- Where's my uncle?</i>

326
00:25:08.975 --> 00:25:10.219
Brock:
<i>Come on.</i>

327
00:25:10.243 --> 00:25:12.087
Wait. did you
just leave him in there?

328
00:25:12.111 --> 00:25:14.890
- Let's go.
- What the fuck?!

329
00:25:14.914 --> 00:25:17.548
Come on.
Let's go.

330
00:25:23.990 --> 00:25:27.736
Lennox tells me
you're grooming
your niece Rebecca

331
00:25:27.760 --> 00:25:30.506
to be your successor.

332
00:25:30.530 --> 00:25:34.565
We'll have to see
if she's up for the task.

333
00:25:37.637 --> 00:25:41.283
I will pray
for your soul. Kai.

334
00:25:41.307 --> 00:25:43.552
But I think
at this point.

335
00:25:43.576 --> 00:25:47.811
even God doesn't know
what to make of you.

336
00:26:00.192 --> 00:26:03.639
Rest in peace.
old friend.

337
00:26:03.663 --> 00:26:05.863
( chuckles )

338
00:26:23.282 --> 00:26:25.916
Lock the door.

339
00:26:50.209 --> 00:26:53.177
I'm gonna enjoy this.

340
00:26:54.814 --> 00:26:56.914
Me. too.

341
00:27:00.186 --> 00:27:03.699
- ( glass shatters )
- Burton!

342
00:27:03.723 --> 00:27:06.357
( shouting )

343
00:27:09.996 --> 00:27:11.862
( screams )

344
00:27:24.243 --> 00:27:26.221
Uncle!

345
00:27:26.245 --> 00:27:29.625
( groaning )

346
00:27:29.649 --> 00:27:32.816
They were going
to burn me.

347
00:27:40.159 --> 00:27:43.293
After my mother died...

348
00:27:44.997 --> 00:27:49.845
I thought that I felt
the grace of God.

349
00:27:49.869 --> 00:27:53.170
I thought He was
calling me back.

350
00:27:54.840 --> 00:27:57.953
That wasn't God.

351
00:27:57.977 --> 00:28:00.389
That was just grief.

352
00:28:00.413 --> 00:28:02.980
An emptiness.

353
00:28:06.085 --> 00:28:09.064
To me belong vengeance
and recompense.

354
00:28:09.088 --> 00:28:13.869
Their foot shall slide
in due time.

355
00:28:13.893 --> 00:28:18.173
<i>The day of their calamity</i>
<i>is at hand.</i>

356
00:28:18.197 --> 00:28:20.409
And the things that shall
come upon them

357
00:28:20.433 --> 00:28:24.735
- make haste.
- <i>( man groaning )</i>

358
00:28:42.455 --> 00:28:45.489
( speaks Pennsylvania Dutch )

359
00:29:02.842 --> 00:29:06.343
<i>( men screaming )</i>

360
00:29:20.493 --> 00:29:23.327
( screams )

361
00:29:50.422 --> 00:29:54.258
<i>( music playing )</i>

362
00:30:00.566 --> 00:30:04.468
<i>� Love is a name �</i>

363
00:30:07.306 --> 00:30:11.141
<i>� In the wind �</i>

364
00:30:14.380 --> 00:30:18.448
<i>� When it blows through �</i>

365
00:30:21.253 --> 00:30:26.390
<i>� The trees and stars �</i>

366
00:30:30.429 --> 00:30:33.041
<i>� They make a wish... �</i>

367
00:30:33.065 --> 00:30:35.310
Hey.

368
00:30:35.334 --> 00:30:38.202
Hey. stay where you are.

369
00:30:41.240 --> 00:30:43.552
Hey. Hey. hey. hey.
Stop.

370
00:30:43.576 --> 00:30:44.853
I need to talk
to the sheriff.

371
00:30:44.877 --> 00:30:47.155
- Yeah. you can talk to him.
- You don't understand.

372
00:30:47.179 --> 00:30:50.392
- He knows me.
- What's your name?

373
00:30:50.416 --> 00:30:51.893
Deva Hopewell.

374
00:30:51.917 --> 00:30:53.094
- You the mayor's kid?
- Yes.

375
00:30:53.118 --> 00:30:55.831
Hey. hey. hey.
Miss Hopewell.
Hey. hey. stop.

376
00:30:55.855 --> 00:30:58.166
Miss Hopewell.
you are under arrest.

377
00:30:58.190 --> 00:30:59.501
You have the right
to remain silent.

378
00:30:59.525 --> 00:31:03.205
Anything you say or do
will be held against you
in a court of law.

379
00:31:03.229 --> 00:31:06.964
( grunting )

380
00:31:28.220 --> 00:31:32.623
- These things take time.
- Yeah.

381
00:31:33.325 --> 00:31:37.227
( grunting )

382
00:31:38.998 --> 00:31:41.509
I can handle it.

383
00:31:41.533 --> 00:31:44.134
( exhales )

384
00:31:45.671 --> 00:31:50.073
- Can you?
- Most of the time.

385
00:31:52.177 --> 00:31:54.322
What the fuck is this?

386
00:31:54.346 --> 00:31:56.424
Jasper. Bryce.

387
00:31:56.448 --> 00:31:58.627
Jesus Christ. Bunker.
You're a fucking pig?

388
00:31:58.651 --> 00:32:01.229
I'm a Banshee
deputy sheriff.

389
00:32:01.253 --> 00:32:02.364
You're a motherfucking
traitor.

390
00:32:02.388 --> 00:32:03.632
I should stab you
through the heart.

391
00:32:03.656 --> 00:32:05.567
Expressing your opinion
isn't a crime.

392
00:32:05.591 --> 00:32:07.369
<i>but threatening</i>
<i>a peace officer is.</i>

393
00:32:07.393 --> 00:32:09.671
So was torching that kike
temple in Harrisburg.

394
00:32:09.695 --> 00:32:13.096
but I don't remember
that stopping you.

395
00:32:14.466 --> 00:32:17.178
- Calvin still running things?
- Damn straight he is.

396
00:32:17.202 --> 00:32:19.214
But if you think he's gonna
protect you from us.

397
00:32:19.238 --> 00:32:22.272
you got another
think coming.

398
00:32:53.172 --> 00:32:57.174
Calvin should have killed you
when he had the chance.

399
00:32:58.310 --> 00:33:02.746
You tell my brother
I'll be seeing him real soon.

400
00:33:04.450 --> 00:33:08.452
<i>( jukebox playing )</i>

401
00:33:08.754 --> 00:33:11.555
Thank you. boys.

402
00:33:16.762 --> 00:33:20.208
Why. Colonel. right?

403
00:33:20.232 --> 00:33:21.710
Were you a military man?

404
00:33:21.734 --> 00:33:24.079
No. just watch
a lot of movies.

405
00:33:24.103 --> 00:33:25.480
What's your poison?

406
00:33:25.504 --> 00:33:28.305
Maker's Mark. neat.

407
00:33:28.474 --> 00:33:30.118
All this time in Banshee

408
00:33:30.142 --> 00:33:33.588
and I've never been
in here before.

409
00:33:33.612 --> 00:33:35.523
Well. it's...

410
00:33:35.547 --> 00:33:36.524
not much to look at.

411
00:33:36.548 --> 00:33:41.262
but at least the roof
doesn't leak.

412
00:33:41.286 --> 00:33:43.520
Hmm.

413
00:33:43.789 --> 00:33:47.669
You know.
the craziest thing
happened the other day.

414
00:33:47.693 --> 00:33:49.571
- Did it?
- Mmm.

415
00:33:49.595 --> 00:33:51.639
Four idiots
decided to steal

416
00:33:51.663 --> 00:33:55.043
a considerable
amount of my money.

417
00:33:55.067 --> 00:33:57.312
Is that so?

418
00:33:57.336 --> 00:34:00.448
Mm. but that's not
the crazy part.

419
00:34:00.472 --> 00:34:06.710
These guys actually
thought they were gonna
get away with it.

420
00:34:11.450 --> 00:34:16.765
See. what you have here
is a lose-lose situation.

421
00:34:16.789 --> 00:34:19.756
I never lose.

422
00:34:22.161 --> 00:34:24.628
Sugar:
<i>Damn it!</i>

423
00:34:34.139 --> 00:34:36.473
Thanks for the drink.

424
00:34:37.142 --> 00:34:39.176
Fuck you.

425
00:34:51.657 --> 00:34:53.857
Job.

426
00:34:55.394 --> 00:34:58.128
Who the fuck are you?

427
00:34:58.363 --> 00:35:00.775
My name is Leo.
Maybe you've heard of me.

428
00:35:00.799 --> 00:35:01.810
Don't flatter yourself.

429
00:35:01.834 --> 00:35:05.380
Well. I've definitely
heard of you. Job.

430
00:35:05.404 --> 00:35:09.406
That's why I doubled
the sedative.

431
00:35:16.782 --> 00:35:19.149
( groans )

432
00:35:20.119 --> 00:35:24.221
This is actually
a very big moment for me.

433
00:35:31.663 --> 00:35:34.164
( alarm chirps )

434
00:36:19.211 --> 00:36:22.445
<i>( footsteps approaching )</i>

435
00:36:27.819 --> 00:36:30.498
- You have to go back for him.
- No. Em. I don't.

436
00:36:30.522 --> 00:36:31.799
- Now come on.
- Well. then I will.

437
00:36:31.823 --> 00:36:33.668
The hell you are.
Em. listen to me.
Listen.

438
00:36:33.692 --> 00:36:36.337
Do you have any idea
how close you came
to dying tonight?

439
00:36:36.361 --> 00:36:38.506
They were going to kill
you because of him.

440
00:36:38.530 --> 00:36:40.775
- Let go of me!
- Jesus Christ!

441
00:36:40.799 --> 00:36:41.709
Open your eyes!

442
00:36:41.733 --> 00:36:44.479
Do you understand?
You are shacking up with
a fucking psychopath.

443
00:36:44.503 --> 00:36:46.781
What. you're going
to let him die because
you're jealous?

444
00:36:46.805 --> 00:36:50.285
Fuck you. Brock!
You coward.

445
00:36:50.309 --> 00:36:52.509
Oh. yeah?

446
00:36:53.812 --> 00:36:56.491
( gunshots )

447
00:36:56.515 --> 00:36:58.193
Oh. fuck!

448
00:36:58.217 --> 00:37:02.586
And you're welcome
for saving your goddamn life.

449
00:37:02.821 --> 00:37:05.655
<i>( door opens )</i>

450
00:37:08.594 --> 00:37:10.927
Sir.

451
00:37:11.997 --> 00:37:13.964
Where is she?

452
00:37:26.378 --> 00:37:29.224
I just need
your signature
on this report

453
00:37:29.248 --> 00:37:30.725
and you can take
your daughter home.

454
00:37:30.749 --> 00:37:33.828
- She's not going home.
- What?

455
00:37:33.852 --> 00:37:37.632
At least not tonight.

456
00:37:37.656 --> 00:37:40.690
Yes. sir.

457
00:37:45.631 --> 00:37:50.567
I'm sorry. Deva.
I don't know what
else to do.

458
00:37:52.904 --> 00:37:55.005
Dad.

459
00:37:55.774 --> 00:37:58.275
Dad!

460
00:38:00.946 --> 00:38:04.447
( crying )

461
00:38:21.366 --> 00:38:22.644
Emily:
<i>Thank God.</i>

462
00:38:22.668 --> 00:38:25.480
<i>I thought you were dead.</i>
<i>Come on.</i>

463
00:38:25.504 --> 00:38:27.515
Okay. we're gonna have
to get you to the hospital.

464
00:38:27.539 --> 00:38:29.484
We're not going
to any hospital.

465
00:38:29.508 --> 00:38:31.552
- Why?
- I made a mistake.

466
00:38:31.576 --> 00:38:33.721
I should never have allowed
things to go this far.

467
00:38:33.745 --> 00:38:35.023
What are you
talking about?

468
00:38:35.047 --> 00:38:36.658
You and I will never
see each other again.

469
00:38:36.682 --> 00:38:40.061
- I... I don't understand.
- Thank you for your services
to my mother.

470
00:38:40.085 --> 00:38:44.487
You'll be compensated
for your time and trouble.

471
00:38:44.856 --> 00:38:46.934
Wait. don't do this. Kai.

472
00:38:46.958 --> 00:38:48.603
I know you're trying
to protect me.

473
00:38:48.627 --> 00:38:51.806
but I'm not afraid
of those men when
I'm with you.

474
00:38:51.830 --> 00:38:54.364
Good-bye.

475
00:38:57.969 --> 00:39:02.105
It's not those men
you need to be afraid of.

476
00:39:08.480 --> 00:39:11.348
<i>( car engine starts )</i>

477
00:39:32.437 --> 00:39:34.571
Hey.

478
00:39:37.542 --> 00:39:39.554
I know this might
be hard to believe.

479
00:39:39.578 --> 00:39:42.357
but your father
thinks he's doing
what's best for you.

480
00:39:42.381 --> 00:39:44.759
He's not really
my father.

481
00:39:44.783 --> 00:39:45.660
Bunker.

482
00:39:45.684 --> 00:39:48.730
Sir. Miss Hopewell
is being held
for possession.

483
00:39:48.754 --> 00:39:52.155
Lucas:
<i>Give me the keys.</i>

484
00:39:54.826 --> 00:39:55.770
Lucas:
<i>Let's go.</i>

485
00:39:55.794 --> 00:39:58.806
With all due respect.
sir. Mayor Hopewell wanted
her to stay overnight.

486
00:39:58.830 --> 00:40:02.432
